## ğŸ“¦ Installation

```bash
pip install aliyah

Useage
from aliyah_predictor import LinearPredictors

# Sample data
X = [[1, 2], [2, 3], [3, 4]]
y = [2, 3, 5]

# Initialize predictor with MALP method
model = LinearPredictors(method="malp")

# Fit and predict
model.fit(X, y)
predictions = model.predict(X)

# Evaluate agreement
metrics = model.evaluate(y, predictions)
print(metrics)

Expected Output

{
    'CCC': 0.98,
    'PCC': 0.99,
    'MSE': 0.12
}

